HEADWORD: Atmolysis
<hw>At*mol"y*sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ vapor
+ <?/ a loosing, <?/ to loose.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The act or
process of separating mingled gases of unequal diffusibility by
transmission through porous substances. See also <er>gaseous
diffusion</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

